<subSubSection id="C34472A7FFF96824459A3282BBBCF866" pageId="12" pageNumber="295" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BE1212CFFF96824459A3282BBBCF866" blockId="12.[151,1436,1821,2027]" pageId="12" pageNumber="295">
<emphasis id="B92AFD3EFFF96824459A3282BB40F82E" bold="true" box="[199,315,1929,1955]" pageId="12" pageNumber="295">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species was previously recorded from many localities in the NT, two sites in northern WA and four sites in northern 
<collectingRegion id="499AEFCEFFF9682444D732A6B875F84A" box="[394,526,1965,1991]" country="Australia" name="Queensland" pageId="12" pageNumber="295">Queensland</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFCF5CDDFFF96824474032A6B8A7F84A" author="Cartwright, D. I." box="[541,732,1965,1991]" pageId="12" pageNumber="295" pagination="1 - 48" refId="ref14543" refString="Cartwright, D. I. (1990) The Australian species of Ecnomus McLachlan (Trichoptera: Ecnomidae). Memoirs of the Museum of Victoria, 51, 1 - 48. https: // doi. org / 10.24199 / j / mmv. 1990.51.01" type="journal article" year="1990">Cartwright 1990</bibRefCitation>
). Here, a further 
<specimenCount id="9D58EAA5FFF9682446C132A6BE5FF84A" box="[924,1060,1965,1991]" pageId="12" pageNumber="295" type="male">seven males</specimenCount>
of this species are recorded from an additional five NT sites.
</paragraph>
